com.ibm.jaggr.core

Interface IVariableResolver


  • public interface IVariableResolver
    Interface for variables resolver. Variables of the form ${varname} which appear in the server-side config JavaScript will be replaced by the values returned from the resolve method. The default variable resolver uses Java system properties.

    Variable resolvers are registered with the service registry using the interface name and the name property set to the name of the aggregator instance.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      String resolve(String variableName)
      Returns the value to use in place of the variable name.

    • Method Detail

      • resolve

        String resolve(String variableName)
        Returns the value to use in place of the variable name. If a resolver cannot resolve a variable name, it should return null.
        Parameters:
        variableName - The variable name
        Returns:
        The value to use, or null.
